Browse, import, and join data

10
00:00:43,791 --> 00:00:48,375
Using the SageMaker Canvas visual interface, you can browse and import your data.

11
00:00:48,625 --> 00:01:01,125
SageMaker canvas supports the import of tabular data, such as CSV, and Parquet.
Import images with JPEG, PNG, and TIFF extensions; as well as document data, such as PDF files.

12
00:01:01,708 --> 00:01:13,625
SageMaker Canvas, can also discover, AWS data sources that your account has access to, including Amazon S3, Amazon RDS, Amazon Redshift, and the AWS Glue Data Catalog.

13
00:01:14,250 --> 00:01:19,833
Or import third-party data from vendors, such as Salesforce, Snowflake, and 40 plus others.

14
00:01:21,125 --> 00:01:23,583
Data analysis with visualizations.

15
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:31,250
SageMaker Canvas, offers built-in exploratory data analysis, so you can prepare, explore, and analyze your data.

16
00:01:31,833 --> 00:01:37,791
SageMaker canvas, makes it easy to impute missing values, and replace outliers with custom values.

17
00:01:38,083 --> 00:01:49,583
SageMaker Canvas, offers a selection of over 300 prebuilt, PySpark-based data transformations, so you can manipulate your data, and scale your data preparation workflow, without writing a single line of code.

18
00:01:50,458 --> 00:01:52,000
Create custom models.

19
00:01:52,333 --> 00:02:01,500
Using Amazon SageMaker Canvas, you can create custom models for classification, regression, forecasting, or image recognition, that are trained using your own data.

20
00:02:01,791 --> 00:02:11,041
SageMaker canvas, also provides access to
ready-to-use foundation models, or FMs, for content generation, text extraction, and text summarization.

21
00:02:12,083 --> 00:02:14,500
SageMaker canvas, use-cases.

22
00:02:14,833 --> 00:02:16,875
Generate or summarize content.

23
00:02:17,166 --> 00:02:27,833
Use Amazon SageMaker canvas, to create personalized, engaging, and high-quality sales and marketing content, such as social media posts, product descriptions, and email campaigns.

24
00:02:28,166 --> 00:02:37,833
Or, produce concise summaries of articles, blog posts, and meeting minutes, to identify the most important data, highlight key takeaways, and more quickly distill information.

25
00:02:39,166 --> 00:02:40,708
Predict customer churn.

26
00:02:41,250 --> 00:02:55,291
You can use SageMaker Canvas, to ingest product consumption data, and purchase history records, to create a model of your customers churn patterns. Then use the model to predict unhappy customers and take actions to convert them into happy and satisfied customers.

27
00:02:56,208 --> 00:02:58,041
Plan inventory efficiently.

28
